cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 

1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with wireless body area networks and communication protocols. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the efficiency of a multi-hop transmission protocol. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper proposes a Markovian analytical model for evaluating the performance of a diffusion-based broadcast protocol. 
4. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is a possible category as the paper deals with the transmission of messages in a network. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) is a possible category as the paper evaluates the performance of the broadcast protocol with respect to various parameters.
